<div class=3D"title_box">
 <h1 class=3D"wims_title">
   <span class=3D"titre">Base converter</span>
  <br class=3D"clearall">
 </h1>
</div>
<!-- end html/title.phtml -->

<p>
  This simple tool allows you to convert a same number between its
 representations under different number systems.
</p><p>
  For example, the number <img src=3D"https://wims.univ-cotedazur.fr/wims/m=
athfonts/109/pi.gif" style=3D"margin:0px; border:none" alt=3D"pi"> is equal=
 to 3.14159... in a decimal system (base 10),
 or to 3.243F6... in a hexadecimal system (base 16), or to 11.001001... in =
a
 binary system (base 2).
</p>
















